The Benue State Independent Electoral Commission (BESIEC) has cancelled the date earlier scheduled for the state council polls and shifted it back to Saturday, 30th April 2022 against Saturday, 7th May 2022. Briefing newsmen in Makurdi on Monday, Chairman of the Commission, Tersoo Loko noted that it had to abridge the date so as avoid a clash with election activities of the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC). According to him, “This to inform the general public, particularly, the electorate and all critical stakeholders in the electoral process that the elections into the 23 Local Government Councils of the state earlier slated for 7th May 2022, will now hold on 30th April 2022 “The new date for the election became necessary in order to avoid the clash with the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) General election timetable. “This is in line with Section 95 of Benue State Electoral (Amendment) Law 2012, which has given the Commission the powers to abridge its timetable.” Loko explained that in the change of date, the commission requires that names of polling agents by political parties be submitted to the Commission from 9am to 4 pm on Monday, 25th April 2022, while campaigns are expected to terminate by midnight of 28th April 2022. He further stated that in the new arrangement, the Commission intends to publish result of the elections on Tuesday, 3rd May 2022, while a re-run of the elections (if any) would hold on Thursday, 5th May 2022. The BESIEC boss who regretted the inconveniences the change in date might have caused the electorate and other stakeholders said the body plans to issue certificates of return to winners of the election on Friday, 5th May, 2022. POLL He, therefore, advised, “All political parties and relevant stakeholders to note the new date on the timetable and follow it accordingly.”